<p>I really find it interesting how little American MSM delves into how Russia and China would react to US/Israel military action against Iran. </p>
<p>It is too obvious that the latest sanctions by America are not aimed at containing Iran, but rather cutting Chinese growth and influence. After all, requiring countries to stop purchasing Iranian oil forces countries to turn to sources that are directly controlled by Americans. And cutting oil purchases may hurt the US a little by driving up world oil prices, but it would hurt China far more.</p>
<p>Putin has made it more than obvious that no one in Russia believes that the US building missile sites in former Soviet states is aimed at Iran, but rather at containing Russia. In fact, if you look at US bases in the ME, it is also very apparent how important it would be to a country like Russia to not lose Iran.</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t think that Russia/China would directly support Iran, at least not in the beginning, but I certainly would expect to see weaponry start flowing in from both of them, and for both those countries to exploit the weak position the war would put the US in to the fullest.</p>
